  "prompt": "Is it possible to change names in savings a/c?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally possible to change the name on a savings account, but the process and requirements can vary depending on the bank or financial institution. The reasons for a name change can include marriage, divorce, legal name changes, or correcting an error. Here are some general steps you might need to follow:\n\n1. **Contact Your Bank**: Reach out to your bank to inquire about their specific process and requirements for changing the name on your account. This can often be done by visiting a local branch, calling customer service, or checking the bank\u2019s website.\n\n2. **Provide Documentation**: You will likely need to provide legal documentation supporting the name change. Common documents include:\n   - Marriage certificate\n   - Divorce decree\n   - Court order\n   - Updated government-issued identification (such as a driver's license or passport)\n   - Social Security card reflecting the new name\n\n3. **Complete Necessary Forms**: The bank may require you to fill out specific forms to process the name change. These forms might need to be signed in person at the branch.\n\n4. **Update Records**: Once the necessary documents and forms are submitted, the bank will update your account information to reflect your new name.\n\n5. **Get Confirmation**: After the name has been changed, request confirmation or documentation from the bank, confirming that your account records have been updated.\n\nRemember, procedures can differ from one financial institution to another, so it\u2019s imperative to check with your specific bank for detailed instructions.",
